{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567056","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567056"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:54:10+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:54:10+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18925"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18925","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18925"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.21,0.76,0.01,0.01,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11658"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80403"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11658","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11658"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18925"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65676"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11367"},{"type":"tags","id":"11369"},{"type":"tags","id":"11370"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27432"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27433"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80403","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80403"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA general practitioner wants to advocate for improved mental health services in their rural community. They have gathered data showing that local residents wait an average of eight weeks to access psychological services, compared to two weeks in metropolitan areas. The community has experienced three youth suicides in the past year.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate first step in developing a health advocacy campaign?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Submit a formal complaint to the health department","Collect and analyse relevant health outcome data","Organise a protest outside local government offices","Start an online petition for more funding","Write letters to local newspapers describing the crisis"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most effective first step is to \u003Cstrong\u003Ecollect and analyse relevant health outcome data\u003C/strong\u003E. Evidence-based advocacy requires comprehensive data to demonstrate the scope of the problem and justify proposed solutions. This includes gathering statistics on wait times, mental health outcomes, service availability, and population needs.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe other approaches are less appropriate initial steps:\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWrite letters to local newspapers describing the crisis\u003C/strong\u003E - While media engagement is important, it should follow proper data collection and analysis to ensure accurate representation of the issues\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOrganise a protest outside local government offices\u003C/strong\u003E - Direct action should only be considered after other systematic approaches have been attempted\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESubmit a formal complaint to the health department\u003C/strong\u003E - Complaints are more effective when supported by comprehensive evidence and specific recommendations\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStart an online petition for more funding\u003C/strong\u003E - Funding requests should be based on detailed needs assessments and clear evidence of service gaps\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E        \u003Cp\u003ESuccessful health advocacy requires a systematic approach beginning with thorough documentation of the problem. This evidence can then inform engagement with stakeholders, media campaigns, and policy recommendations.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Health advocacy involves action taken to influence decision-makers to implement policies that improve population health outcomes.","Evidence-based approaches are essential for effective health advocacy campaigns.","Successful health advocacy requires engagement with multiple stakeholders including community members, healthcare providers, and policymakers."],"references":["Hubinette M, Dobson S, Scott I, Sherbino J. Health advocacy. Med Teach. 2017 Feb;39(2):128-135. doi: 10.1080/0142159X.2017.1245853. Epub 2016 Nov 21. PMID: 27866451. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27866451/","Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 18]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65676"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18925"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65676","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65676"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-20T16:11:20+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-20T16:12:15+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11658"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80403"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/7